##################
##################
General information
##################
##################This is a simple othello game. This game is still under development. I am planning on using this to experiment with neural network learning.

The project uses external SDL2 library for graphics and keyboard/mouse input. Information on SDL is available at https://www.libsdl.org/index.php.



##################
##################
Compiling from source on Ubuntu
##################
##################


Requirements:
##################
cmake:
sudo apt install cmake
SDL2:
sudo apt install libsdl2-dev
SDL_mixer 2.0:
sudo apt install libsdl2-mixer-dev
SDL_image.
sudo apt install libsdl2-image-dev


Compilation
##################
In directory othellogame/
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make
cp -r ../res/ othello/
##################

Copy resource files to the directory with the binary
##################
In directory build/
cp -r ../res/ othello/
##################


Running the game
##################
In directory build/
./othello/othello
##################




